org.apache.taverna.reference

Interface ValueCarryingExternalReference<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, ExternalReferenceSPI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InlineByteArrayReference, InlineStringReference

    public interface ValueCarryingExternalReference<T>
extends ExternalReferenceSPI
    Specialization of ExternalReferenceSPI for reference types which carry a value type internally. Such references can be de-referenced to the specified object type very cheaply. Note that this is not to be used to get an object property of a reference, the returned object must correspond to the value of the referenced data - this means that the HttpUrlReference does not use this to return a java.net.URL, but that the InlineStringReference does use it to return a java.lang.String
    Author:
    Tom Oinn
